<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Liebherr is the German refrigeration name that shows up next to Sub-Zero in Beverly Hills estate kitchens.</h2>

    <p>Liebherr-Hausgeräte GmbH has been making refrigerators out of Ochsenhausen, Baden-Württemberg since 1949 — founded by Hans Liebherr, family-owned through three generations of the Liebherr family, and notably independent of the major appliance conglomerates that absorbed most of its European peers. In our 5-county SoCal service area, Liebherr cluster patterns are specific and telling: Beverly Hills and Bel Air estate kitchens often run Liebherr alongside Sub-Zero (the homeowners shopping at that price tier compare them directly), Hancock Park older homes where 1990s and 2000s renovations brought in the CBN freestanding tier, Pacific Palisades and Newport Coast properties with wine cellars built around WS / WT column installations, and the newer integrated-kitchen specifications in Calabasas / Hidden Hills / Newport Beach remodels favoring the CS integrated counter-depth line.</p>

    <p>Two Liebherr realities shape every service call we run. First, <strong>Liebherr's US product surface is narrow — refrigeration only</strong>. Refrigerators, freezers, wine storage. No washers, dryers, ovens, dishwashers, or microwaves in the US lineup. Service shops that advertise "Liebherr appliance repair" across a full kitchen suite are either confused or fabricating scope; we work the actual scope honestly. Second, <strong>Liebherr parts ship from Germany or Austria</strong>. Common wear items (gaskets, valves, fan motors, BioFresh sensors) we stock on the truck for the dominant CS and CBN model families. Less common items (specific control boards, DuoCooling assemblies, BluPerformance compressor parts) run 7 to 14 day lead time through Liebherr USA's New Jersey distribution back to Ochsenhausen. When we can identify the failure by phone before dispatch, we pre-order — and that's the difference between a 2-visit repair and a 1-visit repair on a Liebherr.</p>

    <p>This page covers Liebherr repair across the full US lineup. Every Liebherr service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Liebherr parts (aftermarket substitutes don't fit or perform to factory spec on this brand), and an honest written quote with parts lead-time disclosed before any work begins.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 REFRIGERATORS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Liebherr refrigerator repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">CS counter-depth integrated, CBN freestanding, ECBN tall integrated, HC column.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Liebherr's US refrigerator lineup splits across four configuration families, each with its own service profile. The CS counter-depth integrated series is the dominant install pattern in current LA luxury remodels; the CBN freestanding line covers the more traditional full-size French Door market.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2015-2019 CS-series BioFresh humidity sensor pattern (most common Liebherr service call in LA)</h3>
      <p>The CS 1200, CS 1311, CS 1360, and surrounding counter-depth integrated production years between roughly 2015 and 2019 develop a consistent BioFresh humidity sensor failure around year 5 to 6. Symptoms: produce wilting in the BioFresh drawer faster than it should, condensation building on the drawer's internal door surface, occasional sensor-error indication on the front control panel. Sensor replacement is the fix; we stock the common Liebherr humidity sensors on the truck for the CS frame dimensions. <strong>$245-$385 typical, same-day when the sensor is in stock.</strong> Worth checking the BioFresh drawer seal and the small circulation fan at the same time — replacing the sensor without inspecting the other two components can produce a half-fixed result.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the BioFresh pattern, Liebherr refrigerator service tree tracks closely with the high-end refrigeration category overall. Most-common service items by year-window:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> ice maker assembly failures on units that have one (door-mounted on certain CBN configurations, internal on others). Replacement runs $345-$525 — heavier-spec than mass-market ice makers, reflects in cost. Water inlet valve often paired ($185-$285).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-7:</strong> BioFresh humidity sensor (above), door gasket compression on heavily-used units ($185-$285), evaporator fan motor ($285-$425).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7-10:</strong> condenser fan motor, defrost system on units that aren't fully NoFrost, main control board ($445-$680), DuoCooling control logic on the dual-circuit models.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10-12:</strong> compressor replacement. BluPerformance compressors on newer units carry an extended warranty (5 years parts on the compressor itself); out-of-warranty replacement runs $880-$1,400 — and on a Liebherr we usually walk you through why the repair makes sense (cabinet has another decade-plus, replacement-unit cost is $8,000-$14,000+).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 12+:</strong> sealed-system refrigerant work, gasket replacement on a full-perimeter basis, hinge alignment if door sag has set in.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The CS series adds integration complexity — flush-mount cabinetry surrounds, custom panel fronts on most installations, ventilation through the integrated kick plate. Service access requires careful cabinet preservation (we use protective padding during any pull-work to prevent panel damage), and reinstall requires alignment to maintain consistent gap lines top/bottom/left/right. Builds in extra time but it's part of working on this product class. ECBN integrated tall units (taller-than-standard column refrigerators meant to flank an integrated freezer column) share the same service approach. HC built-in column units (refrigerator-only columns paired with separate freezer columns) are the closest Liebherr competitor to Sub-Zero column products and tend to install in the largest custom kitchens we work in.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 FREEZERS & WINE STORAGE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, Freezers and wine storage</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">FNB / FN freezer columns and WS / WT / WTes / HWgw wine storage.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Beyond combination refrigerator-freezers, Liebherr's US lineup includes dedicated freezer columns (typically paired with an adjacent refrigerator column in column-style installations) and a substantial wine storage product line that anchors many of the wine cellars we service in Westside and Newport Coast estates.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Freezer columns (FNB, FN series)</h3>
        <p>Standalone freezer columns designed to install alongside a matching refrigerator column for a built-in column-style configuration. NoFrost across the current lineup. Most common service: NoFrost defrost heater or thermostat year 7-10, evaporator fan motor year 8-12, door gasket on heavily-used units. Compressor failure profile mirrors the refrigerator side — built to last, repair economics favor service through year 12-15.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Wine columns (WS, WT, WTes, HWgw)</h3>
        <p>Single-zone (WS), dual-zone (WT, WTes), and humidified-cellar (HWgw) wine storage columns. Sizes from 12-bottle undercounter to 178-bottle integrated columns (WS 17800 is the flagship column we see in LA wine cellars). Service tree: humidity-control sensor (similar to BioFresh failure pattern, year 5-7), temperature differential drift between zones on dual-zone units, condenser fan motor, and the cellar-temperature recovery cycle on HWgw humidified columns. Worth a dedicated <a href="/brands/liebherr-wine-cooler-repair/">Liebherr wine cooler repair page</a> for deeper coverage.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Combined refrigerator-freezer (CBN, CBNPgb)</h3>
        <p>Full-size freestanding combination units. CBN is the workhorse line; CBNPgb is the premium-spec variant with BluPerformance compressor architecture and DuoCooling dual-circuit refrigerant. Service patterns shared with the refrigerator-only configurations; the dual-circuit DuoCooling adds a useful service property — failure in one circuit (refrigerator or freezer) does NOT always affect the other, which means we can sometimes keep half the unit operational while parts ship.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Honest scope — what Liebherr doesn't make in US</h3>
        <p>If you have a Liebherr-branded washer, dryer, oven, dishwasher, or microwave, it's a European-market unit imported separately from Liebherr-Hausgeräte's US lineup, or it's a different brand misidentified. We service Liebherr refrigeration only. For other appliance categories in your kitchen, see the <a href="/services/">services hub</a> for the full scope by appliance type.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 TECHNOLOGIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">04, Liebherr technologies</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">BioFresh, DuoCooling, NoFrost, BluPerformance — the systems that need brand-specific service.</h2>

    <p>Liebherr's engineering identity sits in four named technology systems that show up across the product lineup. Knowing how they work and how they fail is the difference between a Liebherr-trained service call and a generic refrigerator visit.</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>BioFresh.</strong> Humidity-controlled drawer system that holds higher relative humidity than the surrounding fresh-food compartment — designed for produce, herbs, and fresh proteins. Modulated electronically by a humidity sensor inside the drawer. Failure mode: sensor degradation around year 5-7, presents as wilting produce and drawer condensation. Replacement is the fix; we stock common Liebherr humidity sensors on the truck.</li>
      <li><strong>DuoCooling.</strong> Two independent refrigerant circuits — one for the refrigerator compartment, one for the freezer compartment. Engineered to prevent odor and humidity transfer between sections and to allow temperature precision per zone. Service property worth knowing: failure in one circuit does not automatically take out the other, which means we can sometimes keep half the unit operational while parts ship. Common DuoCooling service items: zone-specific evaporator fan motor, refrigerant charge per circuit (EPA 608 certified for both R-134a and R-600a refrigerant variants used across the lineup).</li>
      <li><strong>NoFrost.</strong> Liebherr's frost-free freezer technology — automatic defrost cycle that prevents ice buildup on the evaporator coil. Standard across most current freezer-equipped Liebherr units. Common service items: defrost heater year 8-12, defrost thermostat, drain line clear (the meltwater drain occasionally clogs and produces a freezer-bottom puddle).</li>
      <li><strong>BluPerformance.</strong> Liebherr's compressor and refrigeration system architecture across newer (2018+) US models. Inverter-driven variable-speed compressor with extended 5-year compressor warranty. Service implications: BluPerformance compressors fail less often than older fixed-speed compressors, but when they do fail the replacement compressor is a brand-specific assembly with longer parts lead time than legacy units.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

